710n\r\n\r\nIt comes with Ethernet\r\nAnd USB you bet\r\nThe memory\r\n32MB\r\nBut more you later can get\r\n\r\nIt doesn\'t work with Mac\r\nThat\'s just a plain ol\' fact\r\nBut it looks nice\r\nAnd it this price\r\nSome smiles we should see crack\r\n\r\nThe printer made by Dell\r\nThe printer made by Dell\r\nHi-ho-click-the-button-yo\r\nAnd buy one for yourself.\r\n\r\n--woot.com',NULL,'2007-06-01 09:34:35','The Dell Printer',3),(75,'Flutter, flap, flutter\r\ngo the little wings.\r\nFlutter, flap, flutter.\r\n\r\nRat-a-tat-tat\r\ngoes the silly kitty.\r\nMreoow!\r\n\r\nPounce!  Leap!\r\nThe kitty gives chase.\r\nLunge.  Crouch.\r\n\r\nStupid or brave we\r\ndo not know\r\nbut the butterfly\r\nlands on the kitty\'s nose!\r\n\r\n*blink* *blink-blink*\r\nConfusion abounds,\r\nthe cat is sleepy,\r\nand thus ends our poem.',NULL,'2007-06-07 13:12:59','Kitty +  Butterfly = Cute',1),(76,'Growl, gurgle, inflate and pain.\r\nYou shall suffer again and again.\r\n\r\nDo not eat me\r\nunless you wish\r\nto wish and wish you were a fish!',NULL,'2007-06-07 13:15:06','Revenge of the Beef Stick',1),(77,'Tick-tock\r\ngoes the clock.\r\nCounting down\r\n\'til\r\nMONDAY!!',NULL,'2007-06-07 16:42:36','Tick-tock',1),(78,'Sleep.  Sleep.  Sleep.  Sleep.  Sleep.\r\nOh how I want to sleep, now.\r\nSleep.  Sleep.  Sleep.  Sleep.  Sleep.',NULL,'2007-06-14 15:12:37','Sleep.  A haiku.',1),(79,'Five syllables here\r\nFive syllables just above\r\nFive syllables here',NULL,'2007-06-14 15:15:56','Autological Haiku',3),(80,'dot dot dash dash dot\r\ndash dash dot dash dash dot dot\r\ndot dot dot dot dash',NULL,'2007-06-14 15:18:23','Morse Haiku',3),(81,'I do believe lunch is on the horizon.\r\nIt looms like a giant sandwich.\r\nSpherical like an orange.\r\nTasting of yogurt.\r\nIt comes to fulfill our needs.\r\nThe coming of the lunch.',NULL,'2007-06-19 11:56:51','Lunch Cometh',1),(82,'Stop your equivocating.\r\nAnd stop procrastingating.\r\nLet us rule the world\r\nunder our bronzed fist.\r\nDiscordians!  Unite!\r\nOr . . . just be discordious and chaotic.\r\nYour call really.',NULL,'2007-06-20 14:43:23','Unite',1),(83,'WHY!?!  Why did I get married?\r\nIt\'s been nothing but bliss and pleasure.\r\nWhere is the angst which fueled my poetry?\r\nWhere is the torment which fueled my prose?\r\nAm I too happy to pursue my creativity?\r\nYes!\r\nDamn women.',NULL,'2007-06-20 14:46:09','Anniversaries',1),(84,'Rats.\r\nIn the walls.\r\nScratching.\r\nScratching.\r\n\r\nThey\'re everywhere.\r\nWanting to get out\r\nand feast on\r\nmy corpulent flesh.',NULL,'2007-06-21 16:25:22','Rats',1),(85,'In a quantum world\r\nwhere fish ruled the land\r\nand polar bears were legal tender,\r\nyou and I could be three.\r\n\r\nIn a quantum world\r\nwhere light was liquid\r\nand dust the hue of love\r\nyou and I could share a spleen.\r\n\r\nIn a quantum world\r\nwhere lamps roamed the wilds\r\nand dreams walked the streets\r\nyou and I . . . you and I would be free.',NULL,'2007-06-27 11:11:53','You and I',1),(86,'Bubble, bubble, foil and rubble.\r\nMy server room was hit by a volcano.',NULL,'2007-06-28 11:21:45','Volcanic Computing',1),(87,'\"Forward my packets\" the computer requested.\r\n\"Ok\" replied the refurbished router.\r\n\r\n\"Forward my packets\" another computer requested.\r\n\"Ok\" replied the refurbished router.\r\n\r\n\"Forward my packets\" the third requested.\r\n\"Ok\" replied the refurbished router.\r\n\r\n\"Forward my packets\" the first computer requested.\r\n\"Ok\" replied the refurbished router, \"but only to this address\".\r\n\"you suck\" replied the computer, and the router was thus recycled of its power source.\r\n\r\nThings went on like this, in un-poetic fashion, for many months.\r\nConnections were lost (especially zeroK\'s).\r\n\r\nMany months later, on an otherwise inconspicuous tuesday, the refurbished router wouldn\'t fix itself.\r\n\"BLAST!\" cried its owner as he shopped for a new router.\r\n\r\nThus was the day the router died.',NULL,'2007-07-11 10:01:33','The day the router sort of died; fishbulbv2 is replaced; a new router finds a home.',3),(88,'Flat and pentagon shaped,\r\nhaving 6 corners.\r\nFloating through space\r\non the back of a turtle.\r\nMy home.\r\nEarth.',NULL,'2007-07-12 15:16:20','Flat Earth',1),(89,'North Dakota where\'d you go?\r\nComing from the mind of\r\nsome mad cartographer.\r\nYou never did exist,\r\nbut my you were pretty.\r\n\r\nIdaho, what\'s up with you?\r\nYou persecute zombies,\r\nyet you are yourself a myth.\r\nFreak.',NULL,'2007-07-12 15:18:59','Ode to the Myths',1),(90,'R0535 4R3 R3D, V10l375 4R3 BLU3, 1337 P037RY 5UCK5, BU7 50 D0 Y0U?',NULL,'2007-07-15 21:30:07','R0s3s R 1337!!1111!!',3),(91,'Breaker, breaker, Tango-Charlie!\r\nThe sky is falling!\r\nThe sky is falling!\r\nMayday!\r\nIn July!\r\nBUTTER.',NULL,'2007-07-19 10:05:28','The Emergency Poetry Network',1),(92,'Roses are red\r\nso is violence.\r\nHIYAH!',NULL,'2007-07-26 08:52:44','Kung-fu Poetry',1),(93,'jedediah is an old bugger\r\nscrawny, lightweight\r\nrevolutionary soldier.\r\nBut my beard is more\r\nimpressive.',NULL,'2007-08-02 11:37:21','jedediah',1),(94,'Walking around\r\ndead of night.\r\n\r\nDoing the rounds\r\nready to fight.\r\n\r\nHe is Ken\r\nthe late night troll.\r\n\r\nYo!  What\'s\r\nthe FREQUENCY?!?',NULL,'2007-08-02 11:40:27','Ken\'s Frequency',1),(95,'dowaito, dowaito\r\nman of photoshopped head on glistening hard body.\r\n\r\nMohawk, boots\r\nleather jacket to complete the ensemble.\r\n\r\nO dowaito\r\nwhy do you smell of Mormons?\r\n\r\ndowaito, the\r\nSLC Xian punk programmer supreme!',NULL,'2007-08-02 11:46:02','dowaito',1),(96,'PhotoNut, the man of\r\nindigestible mystery.\r\nWhy do you consume\r\nso many chili dogs?\r\n\r\nPhotoNut, we\'ve learned\r\nnot to query your name\r\nin the urban dictionary.\r\nEeeew.\r\n\r\nPhotoNut . . . \r\nlol\r\nLONG LINK!\r\nlol',NULL,'2007-08-02 11:48:41','PhotoNut',1),(97,'Oh nev, why do you hate symbols so?\r\nPlagued by the dread of PHP you are,\r\nAn ugly language with broken comparitors.\r\n\r\nPerhaps re-indocrination is all that\'s needed,\r\nTo see, that symbols are the way of the future.\r\nLong live ruby.',NULL,'2007-08-13 09:58:03','symbols',3),(98,'clear\r\n10-4\r\nroger wilco\r\nwhere\'s waldo',NULL,'2007-08-23 09:36:16','Eating Lampshades',2),(99,'Buzz, buzz, buzzing along\r\nto the happy drone\r\nof a snoring sleeper.\r\n\r\nBliss and ignorance\r\nmay not unite\r\nbut sleep, oh sleep,\r\nyou are bliss and make me ignorant of wakefulness.\r\n\r\nSleep. I need you, \'cuz this poem doesn\'t make sense much at all.',NULL,'2007-08-23 16:52:38','Sleep part Zzz',1),(100,'Dough, the stuff I work hard for.\r\nRay some blind guy who played jazz.\r\nMi-go, some crazy-scary monsters!\r\nFa, an element I just discovered!!\r\nSo you need give me praise\r\nLa-yer it good and thick.\r\nTea is what I drink.\r\nDoh!',NULL,'2007-08-30 13:17:51','The Sound of . . . WHAT?',1),(101,'This day of heat\r\njust can\'t be beat.\r\nBut be wary\r\nor you\'ll be visited by the Heat Stroke Fairy!',NULL,'2007-08-30 16:22:00','Heat Stroke',1),(102,'Up and down,\r\nup and down.\r\nUp and down\r\nI think I\'ll wear a frown.\r\n\r\nUp and down,\r\nup and down.\r\nGah!  I\'m calling in sick,\r\nSICK OF STAIRS!\r\n\r\nJet pack me baby!',NULL,'2007-09-06 16:21:22','Stairs',1),(103,'Condensing moisture in the air\r\nhumid, humid everywhere.\r\nOh server room, so cold\r\nand frigid.\r\nYou are now our walk-in\r\nhumidor!\r\n\r\nCold as night, muggy as urban metropolises with a high crime rate,\r\nYou o server room\r\nare not so pleasant anymore.\r\nTo whit!  Forsooth!  Ah phooey,\r\nsomebody fix the humidifying dehumidifier!',NULL,'2007-09-13 13:27:06','CONDENSING MOISTURE',1),(104,'Left!  Right!  A! B!\r\nUp-down-up-down.\r\nLeft, left, left!\r\nAh SNES, how I don\'t miss your ROM.',NULL,'2007-09-13 13:38:18','Retro Gaming',1),(105,'Gather round, all who hear,\r\nand witness my sage advice.\r\nThey come, they come without fear,\r\nthey come to feast upon our flesh.\r\n\r\nShambling, moaning, groaning\r\nthey come, but slowly.\r\nArm thyselves with weapons of\r\nhead-wounding.\r\n\r\nMockery of crockery shall no longer persist,\r\nonce it be known that such shall save our doomed race.\r\nBats, too, sticks, clubs, crowbars,\r\nall shall prove useful against the undead hordes.\r\n\r\nAim for the head, or you\'ll be dead.\r\nDestroy the brain, or remove the head.\r\nThis will stop their locomotion\r\nand quell their ungodly hunger.\r\n\r\nChoose your weapon.\r\nAim for the head.\r\nDON\'T MISS!\r\n(or they will eat your brains)',NULL,'2007-09-20 14:03:41','AIM FOR THE HEAD',NULL),(106,'Falling.\r\nFalling.\r\nPlummeting toward doom.\r\nCascading petals\r\nof lost sanity.',NULL,'2007-09-21 12:54:55','!Sane == TRUE',1),(107,'Back from hiatus\r\nHe says he will blog again\r\nHow long will it last?',NULL,'2007-09-27 09:43:57','blog.0k',3);
